The DPP has accused the Labour ministry of not doing enough to reduce increased cases of child trafficking and exploitation. Noordin Haji’s office says the ministry lacks accurate data on the number of children affected, hurting administration of justice. Prosecutor Everlyne Achieng yesterday said the ministry lacks important data on reported cases. She added that inadequate funds are also a problem. “As you are aware, some of the affected children are traumatised. We need enough money to even hire psychologists to advice them.” Achieng said it is regrettable that some of the affected children are radicalised. Click
